metadata.name: PublicFeed #get with an account passed in excludes statuses from accounts from personally blocked domains

sql_query.sql: SELECT 1 AS one FROM "accounts" WHERE LOWER("accounts"."username") = 'elise_torphy2314' AND LOWER("accounts"."domain") = 'example.com' LIMIT $1
SELECT 1 AS one FROM "instances" WHERE "instances"."domain" = $1 LIMIT $2
SELECT 1 AS one FROM "account_domain_blocks" WHERE "account_domain_blocks"."domain" = $1 AND "account_domain_blocks"."account_id" = $2 LIMIT $3
SELECT 1 AS one FROM "statuses" WHERE "statuses"."uri" = $1 LIMIT $2

INSERT INTO account_stats(account_id, statuses_count, created_at, updated_at, last_status_at) VALUES (111361352191560633, 1, now(), now(), now()) ON CONFLICT (account_id) DO UPDATE SET statuses_count = account_stats.statuses_count + 1, last_status_at = now(), updated_at = now() RETURNING id;

SELECT "statuses"."id", "statuses"."updated_at" FROM "statuses" INNER JOIN "accounts" ON "accounts"."id" = "statuses"."account_id" WHERE "statuses"."visibility" = $1 AND "accounts"."suspended_at" IS NULL AND "accounts"."silenced_at" IS NULL AND (statuses.reply = FALSE OR statuses.in_reply_to_account_id = statuses.account_id) AND "statuses"."reblog_of_id" IS NULL AND 1=1 AND "statuses"."deleted_at" IS NULL AND (accounts.domain IS NULL OR accounts.domain NOT IN ('example.com')) ORDER BY "statuses"."id" DESC LIMIT $2
